from Red Tape, Iron Nerve: The Iranian Quest for U.S. Education by Steven Ditto
Young Iranians increasingly seek international education as their sole means to experience the
broader world pursue economic opportunity, and escape social and political repression in Iran.
Since the mid-2000s, the U.S. State Department has sought to engage Iranian students,
including explicitly exempting exchanges and education-related companies from sanctions.
